    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Front Cover and Related Components -
        Inspection - Checking Upper Idler Gear Backlash
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Checking Upper Idler Gear Backlash</title>
        <figure id="f2650631" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh06/H06048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking upper idler gear backlash</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial indicator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Upper idler gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount a dial indicator on top of the crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the tip of the dial indicator as tangent as possible to a gear tooth and zero dial
                indicator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a screwdriver between the crankshaft and the lower idler gear to keep the lower idler
                gear from rotating.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rock upper idler gear back and forth. Record the reading on the dial indicator face. If the
                backlash exceeds specifications, replace upper idler gear.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
